<p>
It was built as a <%= link_to "Sinatra", "http://www.sinatrarb.com/"  %> web service, simply acting as a frontend to a popular emulator database, allowing the user to navigate &amp; preview app for various systems, and download / run them locally. The <b>RetroFlix</b> application itself is offered as a lightweight <%= link_to "Microservice", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microservices" %> simply acting as a proxy to the required various underlying components. It's fairly simple to setup &amp; install (see the <b><%= link_to "README", "https://github.com/movitto/retroflix/blob/master/README.md" %></b>), and builds upon existing emulators &amp; components the user has locally.
</p>

<p>
As with everything else, it's still a work in progress, but it already sufficing to relive classic memories!
</p>


